last_episode_to_air.name: The Sinner and the Saint
last_episode_to_air.overview: A troubled young man befriends Jessica Vega via social media, and the kind-hearted college student and single mom does her best to steer him towards a better path. Unfortunately, her good intentions will soon come back to haunt her.

name: Dead Silent
overview: A snap of a twig. A rustling leaf. In the woods, myth, urban legend, and horror collide with real-life killers. Transporting viewers into a vortex of dark mystery and psychological terror, each episode tells the true story of a crime set in a desolate location.

episodes.name: The Curse of Dismal Creek
episodes.overview: Sean Farmer travels to a remote campsite in Virginia for a fishing trip with his friend Scott Johnston. When a mysterious stranger appears, the areaâ€™s dark past returns to haunt the campers.

episodes.name: Welcome to the Devil House
episodes.overview: A mansion deep in the Georgia woods is said to house terrible secrets. Everyone in this rural county has heard the rumors, but no one knows the truth ... until a 1982 visit to Corpsewood Manor by a group of young locals turns deadly.

episodes.name: The Stranger on the Hill
episodes.overview: In 2002, a late-night drive to spend time together in a secluded Texas area nicknamed "The Hill" leads to a night of terror for college sweethearts Ashley and Michael.

episodes.name: Madness on the Lake
episodes.overview: The case of Larry Cragun, a resident of a remote lakeside town in Idaho who found the quietness of the community disturbing.

episodes.name: A Killer in the Swamp
episodes.overview: A young woman moves to the Ocala National Forest in Florida in search of peace and a fresh start, but the remote paradise turns out to be the opposite of what she hoped.

episodes.name: The Desert Drifter
episodes.overview: In the peaceful and secluded desert of California's Indian Creek, three teenagers are looking for an adventure, and find a drifter who is on a mission to kill.

episodes.name: Till Death Do Us Part
episodes.overview: In 1988, Doug and Rozina Anderson's decision to spend a long weekend in the peaceful woods of Northern California turns out to be a fateful mistake.

episodes.name: Run for Your Life
episodes.overview: In an Oklahoma town, Amanda Burney and her fiancÃ©, Ethan Walton, run an errand that turns into a run for their lives.

episodes.name: Strange Passenger
episodes.overview: Friends Liz Reiser and Brandi Hicks go to a video store where they give a ride to a stranger in the parking lot, turning their plans for a movie night into a real-life horror film.

episodes.name: Fatal Friendship
episodes.overview: Recent high-school graduate Stephanie Neiman gives her friend a ride, which ends with Neiman fighting for her life.

episodes.name: A History of Violence
episodes.overview: In 1979, a walk in the woods turns out to be a deadly mistake for single mother Marie Huckins; then, 20 years later, her daughter, Patricia, finds herself following in the same fateful footsteps.

episodes.name: Secrets of the Santa Cruz Mountains
episodes.overview: In Santa Cruz, Calif., 19-year-old Linda Jozavich vanishes from work one night in 1979; then, years later, the murder of another local teenager, Lois Sigala, gives investigators a lead that puts them one step closer to solving Jozavich's case.

episodes.name: Picture of Evil
episodes.overview: A picture-perfect dinner for two dissolves into a nightmare for college sophomore Dominique Nicky Hurd and a fellow classmate after they become the targets of a deranged predator.

episodes.name: Out in the Sticks
episodes.overview: Heather Young and her boyfriend, Gary,  relocate to Onoway, MI, in the tranquil Lower Peninsula, for a fresh start. After a couple months, a nasty fight leads to an explosive and terrifying outcome.

episodes.name: Savage Country
episodes.overview: On their way to Oregon in January 1981, young lovers Kevin Thorpe and Laura Craig come face to face with evil on the mountainous, desolate back roads of Northern California.

episodes.name: Get Out
episodes.overview: Young love leads 15-year-old Jessica Keen down an increasingly rebellious path that culminates in a night of grave and unfathomable terror in rural Madison County, Ohio.

episodes.name: Taken For A Ride
episodes.overview: Reeling from a recent breakup, 23-year-old Jacey McWilliams is down in the dumps until she meets a hot, new man; just as they're about to take their relationship to the next level, it takes a horrific turn.

episodes.name: When a Stranger Knocks
episodes.overview: After fleeing her troubled marriage, Deborah Brown and her children seek refuge at her brotherâ€™s house in rustic Lebanon, Maine. When a stranger shows up in the dead of night, Deborah and her family are unprepared for what happens next.

episodes.name: Quiet the Dogs
episodes.overview: Native Texans Connie Hilton and her husband George Newman moved out to rural Tyler, TX. Very early one morning in September 1990, their peaceful country life is abruptly and brutally shattered.

episodes.name: The Creek Bottom
episodes.overview: In March 1987, college student and aspiring teacher Tammy Crowe has everything, including a loving family, a devoted boyfriend, and a promising future; however, on her way to a friend's dinner party, Tammy's life takes a devastating and violent turn.

episodes.name: The Girl on the Billboard
episodes.overview: After 15-year-old Jasmine Block mysteriously vanishes into thin air, her mother Sarah launches a crusade to find her before it's too late. But when the sickening truth behind Jasmine's disappearance surfaces, it leaves Sarah in shock.

episodes.name: The Red River
episodes.overview: After Allison Walker mysteriously goes missing just days before Christmas, investigators scour her pig farm in Adairville, KY, in search of clues. They quickly discover that the deep, dark secret to her whereabouts lies within her own family.

episodes.name: The Torture Chamber
episodes.overview: When Lisa Holden has a baby, gets married and then moves to an isolated home in rural Ben Wheeler, TX, it triggers a long, inexplicable estrangement from her family. But at the root of this painful divide lies something far more evil than her family could ever imagine.

episodes.name: Open 24 Hours
episodes.overview: To pay for college in the summer of 1979, Donna Ferres takes a job working the overnight shift at a local convenience store in Glen Burnie, MD. But after a familiar face walks into the store one night, her routine shift takes a sick and twisted turn.

episodes.name: All the Lights Were On
episodes.overview: After getting engaged, Nikki Ansley takes a job at a local convenience store to pay for her upcoming nuptials. But her best-laid plans are horrifically derailed when two unwelcome customers show up right before closing time.

episodes.name: Three Miles on Castle Rock Road
episodes.overview: After a young Native American woman is found brutalized and clinging to life on the side of a rural Montana road, her family and authorities seek answers. Their search for justice leads them down a shocking, sickening, and devastating road.

episodes.name: The Bodies in the Bunker
episodes.overview: When 16-year-old aspiring film producer Bohdi Potter and her boyfriend go missing, the grave truth behind their disappearance lies deep in the hollow corridors and dark caverns of an old, abandoned military bunker.

episodes.name: The Model Home Murders
episodes.overview: Between her upcoming wedding, a new home, and a thriving real estate career, it looks like everything in Lori Brown's life is headed in the right direction. But one fateful Monday afternoon, her life takes an unforeseeable and tragic turn.
